text: Okay, so I'll admit it. I'm back. Halloween and all! Love your channel and the cool horror trailers! I love your attention to detail, arrangement, music, suspense, mystery, and build-up.This one is still my favorite. I watched Yours when it first came out, then, I watched the studio movie trailer when it came out, then, I watched the studio movie in the theater when it came out. Verdict:  The studio movie was okay I guess.... I would call it cute and mildly spooky, not great, mostly predictable, some of the production was simply substandard.....so, the connection to the other hit movies sets us up for a let down, we expected greatness.... their trailer gives away that it's going to be average. But, when I crave that good old fashioned creeped-out feeling of having to look over my shoulder. I watch the trailer by Sweet Li. You really did quite an amazing creative production here and indeed had the proper elements to creep-out us horror fans!! BTW I love Your "Hell on Earth" trailer too -- creepily delectable!! HAPPY HALLOWEEN SWEET LI.
